This paper addresses the problem of dense pixel correspondence estimation between two images, which is a common task in computer vision. The proposed method uses a CNN-based framework, which is a popular approach in the field of computer vision and machine learning, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of synthetic data for training, which is a common technique in computer vision research, further supporting the possibility of it belonging to cs.CV. Additionally, the paper addresses the problem of relative camera pose estimation, which involves geometric transformations, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics) or cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach that extends existing methods, indicating that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well.
